The Hawks have arrested a 53-year-old woman and her 29-year-old son for dealing in illicit hydroponic cannabis valued at approximately R3 million. The Hawks received a tip-off about a clandestine hydroponic laboratory at a house in Sandhurst where dagga was being planted and processed. Dagga manufacturing equipment, chemicals and dagga plants were seized. The pair is expected to appear at the Randburg Magistrate’s Court on Friday to face charges of dealing in dagga. On Tuesday the Hawks arrested a 36-year-old man for dealing in narcotics – Methcathinone (CAT) with a street value of approximately R2 million. Chigozie Udohe appeared before the Benoni Magistrate’s Court on Wednesday. The case was postponed to February 20, for a formal bail application. -TNA Reporter 